%section.features
  .spacer120
  .container
    %header.text-center
      %h2 The power of CSS
    .spacer120
    .row
      .col-md-6.text-center.m100p
        %figure
          %img{:src => "https://res.cloudinary.com/hilnmyskv/image/upload/v1461179932/illus-feat-faceted.svg", :alt => ""}/

      .col-md-6
        %h3.bold Offline mode
        %p
          Imagine an API Client that doesn't need to make API calls. As long as you've downloaded the initial CSS file, 
          you can search even without an internet connection. That's what we call Offline Search!




    .spacer120
    .row
      .col-md-6.text-center.m100p
        %figure
          %img{:src => "https://res.cloudinary.com/hilnmyskv/image/upload/v1461179932/illus-feat-faceted.svg", :alt => ""}/

      .col-md-6
        %h3.bold No JavaScript needed
        %p
          Stop wasting time wondering if you should put your CSS inside your JS or in a separate file. 
          CSS is so powerful that you won't be needing JavaScript anymore. That's right, we decided to get rid of JavaScript altogether.

    .spacer120
    .row
      .col-md-6.text-center.m100p
        %figure
          %img{:src => "https://res.cloudinary.com/hilnmyskv/image/upload/v1461179932/illus-feat-faceted.svg", :alt => ""}/

      .col-md-6
        %h3.bold Flexbox
        %p
          What would CSS be without flexbox? Flexbox is the best thing that happened to the web since the <code>blink</code> tag.
          With it you can solve one of the most complex tech challenges: vertically centering any element! With such power, building a search engine was a breeze.



